Class SimplexStream.Stack.StackIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.math.plex.SimplexStream.Stack.StackIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<Simplex>
    Enclosing class:
    SimplexStream.Stack

    protected static class SimplexStream.Stack.StackIterator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<Simplex>
    Instances provide Iterator for non-destructive iterating over Stack entries. That is, repeated iteration over a Stack instance is possible with multiple instances of this class.

        public Simplex next()
        Returns the next Simplex in the iteration of the Stack. Used in concert with the hasNext() method returns return each Simplex in the Stack exactly once. Does not have any side effects on the stream.
